[ti:Twinkle, Twinkle, Little Star]
[ar:DCoetzee]
[al:Wikimedia Commons contributions]
[au:Jane Taylor]
[length:02:06]

[00:00.48]Twinkle, twinkle, little star,
[00:05.03]How I wonder what you are!
[00:09.48]Up above the world so high,
[00:13.92]Like a diamond in the sky.

[00:18.60]When the blazing sun is gone,
[00:23.03]When he nothing shines upon,
[00:27.58]Then you show your little light,
[00:32.08]Twinkle, twinkle, all the night.

[00:36.68]Then the trav'ller in the dark,
[00:40.97]Thanks you for your tiny spark,
[00:45.50]He could not see which way to go,
[00:50.17]If you did not twinkle so.

[00:54.80]In the dark blue sky you keep,
[00:59.10]And often thro' my curtains peep,
[01:03.88]For you never shut your eye,
[01:08.45]Till the sun is in the sky.

[01:13.05]As your bright and tiny spark,
[01:17.70]Lights the trav'ller in the dark:
[01:22.33]Tho' I know not what you are,
[01:26.64]Twinkle, twinkle, little star.

[01:31.40]Twinkle, twinkle, little star,
[01:36.08]How I wonder what you are!
[01:40.63]Up above the world so high,
[01:45.20]Like a diamond in the sky.

[01:49.97]Twinkle, twinkle, little star,
[01:54.73]How I wonder what you are!
[01:59.60]How I wonder what you are!
